        <p>So what is gender identity? Gender identity refers to an individual&rsquo;s personal association of belonging to a certain gender group (or none at all). Typically in Western society gender is viewed in a binary; either male or female and often associated with their biological genitalia. However this fails to capture all of the nuances that exist within humanity, thus a gender spectrum is more appropriate. Non-binary gender exists throughout the world, expanding across different cultures and continents throughout history. In the United States, our society teaches children from the time they are born that they must fit in either the &ldquo;boy&rdquo; or the &ldquo;girl&rdquo; category. We give them pink or blue toys and clothing, all in an attempt to ensure they conform to our pre-defined gender binary. Steven Universe helps to smash our so-called gender boxes.</p>

        <p>While some of the characters use she/her pronouns and may &ldquo;present&rdquo; as women, all gems with the exception of Steven are genderless and refer to themselves in the terms they choose. As well as the agender aspect, multiple Gems can become one entity through the process of &ldquo;fusion&rdquo;. Side note: fusion is an adorable dance sequence wherein the Gems get their groove on and turn into a giant ball of light, it&rsquo;s glorious. </p>

